<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Engine_power">Engine power<=
/h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPower-to-wei=
ght_ratio&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Engine =
power"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span>=
</span></div>
<p>The useful power of an engine with shaft power output can be calculated =
using a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamometer" title=3D"Dyna=
mometer">dynamometer</a> to measure <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Torque" title=3D"Torque">torque</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Rotational_speed" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Rotational speed">=
rotational speed</a>, with maximum power reached when torque multiplied by =
rotational speed is a maximum. For jet engines the useful power is equal to=
 the flight speed of the aircraft multiplied by the force, known as net thr=
ust, required to make it go at that speed. It is used when calculating <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propulsive_efficiency" title=3D"Propul=
sive efficiency">propulsive efficiency</a>.
</p>
