=3D9" title=3D"Edit section: Fluid engines and fluid pumps"><span>edit</spa=
n></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid" title=3D"Fluid">Fluids (=
liquid and gas)</a> can be used to transmit and/or store energy using <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pressure" title=3D"Pressure">pressure</=
a> and other fluid properties. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyd=
raulic" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hydraulic">Hydraulic (liquid)</a> an=
d <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pneumatic" class=3D"mw-redirect"=
 title=3D"Pneumatic">pneumatic (gas)</a> engines convert fluid pressure int=
o other desirable <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Work_(physics)" =
title=3D"Work (physics)">mechanical or electrical work</a>. Fluid pumps con=
vert mechanical or electrical work into movement or pressure changes of a f=
luid, or storage in a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pressure_ves=
sel" title=3D"Pressure vessel">pressure vessel</a>.
</p>
