<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Fuel_cell_stacks_and_flow_c=
ell_batteries">Fuel cell stacks and flow cell batteries</h4><span class=3D"=
mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPower-to-weight_ratio&amp;actio=
n=3Dedit&amp;section=3D14" title=3D"Edit section: Fuel cell stacks and flow=
 cell batteries"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket=
">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel_cell" title=3D"Fuel cell">=
Fuel cells</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flow_battery" t=
itle=3D"Flow battery">flow cells</a>, although perhaps using similar chemis=
try to batteries, do not contain the energy storage medium or <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel" title=3D"Fuel">fuel</a>. With a continuou=
s flow of fuel and oxidant, available fuel cells and flow cells continue to=
 convert the energy storage medium into electric energy and waste products.=
 Fuel cells distinctly contain a fixed electrolyte whereas flow cells also =
require a continuous flow of electrolyte. Flow cells typically have the fue=
l dissolved in the electrolyte.
</p>
