<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Utility_and_practical_vehic=
les">Utility and practical vehicles</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/w/index.php?title=3DPower-to-weight_ratio&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=
=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Utility and practical vehicles"><span>edit</s=
pan></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Most vehicles are designed to meet passenger comfort and cargo carrying =
requirements. Vehicle designs trade off power-to-weight ratio to increase c=
omfort, cargo space, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuel_economy_=
in_automobiles" title=3D"Fuel economy in automobiles">fuel economy</a>, <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automobile_emissions_control" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Automobile emissions control">emissions control</=
a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energy_security" title=3D"Ener=
gy security">energy security</a> and endurance. <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Automotive_aerodynamics" title=3D"Automotive aerodynamics">Re=
duced drag</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Low-rolling_res=
istance_tyres" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Low-rolling resistance tyres"=
>lower rolling resistance</a> in a vehicle design can facilitate increased =
cargo space without increase in the (zero cargo) power-to-weight ratio. Thi=
s increases the role flexibility of the vehicle. Energy security considerat=
ions can trade off power (typically decreased) and weight (typically increa=
sed), and therefore power-to-weight ratio, for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Flexible_fuel_vehicle" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Flexible=
 fuel vehicle">fuel flexibility</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Hybrid_vehicle" title=3D"Hybrid vehicle">drive-train hybridisation</a>=
. Some utility and practical vehicle variants such as <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hot_hatch" title=3D"Hot hatch">hot hatches</a> and <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SUV" title=3D"SUV">sports-utility vehi=
cles</a> reconfigure power (typically increased) and weight to provide the =
perception of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sports_car" title=3D=
